			"description": "Three-point one-loop function with three massless internal propagators, used as the primary worked example of the diagrammatic coaction: the coaction of the triangle is written as a sum over pinches (bubbles obtained by pinching one propagator) tensored with the corresponding cut triangles, plus the triangle itself tensored with its maximal cut. Scaleless tadpole pinches are discarded. The consistency of the coaction is checked by expanding in $\\varepsilon$ up to weight 4 and matching against the Goncharov-Brown coaction on MPLs.",
